{
  "message": "feat: add utility infrastructure for advanced styling\n\nAdded class name utility and supporting dependencies for more sophisticated component styling:\n\nNEW FILE: lib/utils.ts\n- Created cn() utility function using clsx + tailwind-merge\n- Combines multiple class names with conflict resolution\n- Standard pattern from shadcn/ui for Tailwind utilities\n- Enables conditional and merged className patterns\n\nExample usage:\n```tsx\ncn('px-2 py-1', isActive && 'bg-blue-500', className)\n// Intelligently merges Tailwind classes, resolves conflicts\n```\n\nDependencies Added (package.json):\n1. clsx (^2.1.1)\n   - Lightweight utility for constructing className strings\n   - Conditional class application\n   - Handles arrays, objects, and mixed inputs\n   - 1.1KB minified\n\n2. tailwind-merge (^3.4.0)\n   - Merges Tailwind classes without conflicts\n   - Resolves duplicate utility classes (e.g., px-2 + px-4 = px-4)\n   - Essential for component libraries with className props\n   - Optimized for Tailwind v3/v4\n\n3. lenis (^1.3.15)\n   - Smooth scroll library\n   - GPU-accelerated scroll animations\n   - Better than native smooth-scroll\n   - ~5KB minified\n   - Will be used for enhanced page transitions\n\nLock File Update (bun.lock):\n- Updated dependency resolution for new packages\n- Includes transitive dependencies\n- Ensures reproducible builds across environments\n\nUse Cases:\n- Component libraries with className prop overrides\n- Conditional styling based on state\n- Merging default + user-provided classes\n- Preventing Tailwind class conflicts in composed components\n\nTechnical Benefits:\n- Type-safe (ClassValue from clsx)\n- Tree-shakeable\n- No runtime overhead (compile-time optimization)\n- Works seamlessly with Tailwind v4\n- Standard pattern recognized by developers\n\nThis infrastructure enables more sophisticated component composition\npatterns used in the upcoming design system refinements.",
